======================================================================
H AS SYMMETRIC FUNCTION OF COMPLEX EIGENVALUES
======================================================================

H depends on the COMPLEX eigenvalue multiset, not just magnitudes.
For circulant tournaments, the relevant symmetric functions are
the power sums p_k = Σ λ_j^k (complex).

Since eigenvalues come in conjugate pairs λ_j, conj(λ_j):
  p_k = 2 * Σ Re(λ_j^k) for j=1,...,(p-1)/2
  = 2 * Σ |λ_j|^k * cos(k * arg(λ_j))

So the PHASES matter, not just magnitudes!

